 theorem for cartesian closed bicategories. In contrast to\nprevious coherence results for bicategories, the argument does not rely on the\ntheory of rewriting or strictify using the Yoneda embedding. Along the way I\nprove bicategorical generalisations of a series of well-established\ncategory-theoretic results, present a notion of glueing of bicategories, and\nbicategorify the folklore result providing sufficient conditions for a glueing\ncategory to be cartesian closed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Jul 2020 17:17:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-02"}
